abstract: Former New York Mayor Mike Bloomberg has plunged over $400 million of his personal fortune into his campaign for the Democratic presidential nomination, an astronomical sum that has led many of his rivals to charge that he is trying to buy the crown.
snippet: Former New York Mayor Mike Bloomberg has plunged over $400 million of his personal fortune into his campaign for the Democratic presidential nomination, an astronomical sum that has led many of his rivals to charge that he is trying to buy the cro...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Former New York Mayor Mike Bloomberg has plunged over $400 million of his personal fortune into his campaign for the Democratic presidential nomination, an astronomical sum that has led many of his rivals to charge that he is trying to buy the crown.

abstract: Joe Biden and Pete Buttigieg, facing increasing pressure to slow the Vermont senator’s rise before Super Tuesday, criticized his record on gun control and his chances against President Trump.
snippet: Joe Biden and Pete Buttigieg, facing increasing pressure to slow the Vermont senator’s rise before Super Tuesday, criticized his record on gun control and his chances against President Trump.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — The day after a Democratic presidential debate brought out the candidates’ outrage at Michael R. Bloomberg, the focus turned back toward Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont, who leads polls of Nevada, California and the nation.

abstract: The top six candidates competing for the Democratic nomination to take on U.S. President Donald Trump in November participated in the ninth presidential debate on Wednesday, with one quickly becoming the focus: Michael Bloomberg.
snippet: The top six candidates competing for the Democratic nomination to take on U.S. President Donald Trump in November participated in the ninth presidential debate on Wednesday, with one quickly becoming the focus: Michael Bloomberg.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — The top six candidates competing for the Democratic nomination to take on U.S. President Donald Trump in November participated in the ninth presidential debate on Wednesday, with one quickly becoming the focus: Michael Bloomberg.
headline_main: Bloomberg Gets a Lashing From Democrats: Key Quotes From a Fiery Debate
headline_print_headline: Bloomberg Gets a Lashing From Democrats: Key Quotes From a Fiery Debate

abstract: Mike Bloomberg has spent over $400 million during his ascent in Democratic primary polls. Money couldn’t save him from a widely panned performance onstage.

abstract: In the last few presidential debates, there was little consensus on a clear winner or loser. That changed on Wednesday night.
snippet: In the last few presidential debates, there was little consensus on a clear winner or loser. That changed on Wednesday night.
lead_paragraph: Twitter can’t tell us whether, or how, Wednesday’s debate might change voters’ minds. But it can give us the perspectives of some of the people with expertise on primary races: veteran campaign strategists, consultants and analysts.

headline_main: Who Won the Democratic Debate? Experts Weigh In

abstract: The world is indifferent to our fate.
snippet: The world is indifferent to our fate.
lead_paragraph: The story of a disaster is, almost by definition, a survivor’s story: If there are no survivors, there is not much of a story. The Old Testament has its Noahs and Lots, figures that God spares so their tales of floods, plagues, famines and massacres can be told, their lessons absorbed by the living. In the final scene of “Moby-Dick,” Ishmael circles the sinking wreck of Captain Ahab’s Pequod, clinging to a buoyant coffin and a verse from Job: “And I only am escaped alone to tell thee.”
